00:00:08,012 --> 00:00:23,352
Hi, hello, welcome back to our channel! This Sunday I am going to show you how to make Dindigul special Talapakatti Chicken Biryani. This biryani will be spicy with a unique flavor, so let’s see how to prepare this Dindigul biryani.

2
00:00:28,347 --> 00:00:55,634
Before preparing the Dindigul Talapakatti Biryani, take half a cup of chopped onions, half a green chili, some ginger, garlic, a little coriander, and a quarter cup of mint leaves in a mixer jar and grind them to a paste.

3
00:00:57,472 --> 00:01:24,861
Take 2 mace, 2 bay leaves, and 6 cloves (more spice ingredients follow, cut off in original).

4
00:01:28,861 --> 00:01:50,765
Biryani masala is ready. Next, to prepare the biryani, heat half a cup of oil and 2 tablespoons of ghee in a vessel. Add the ground paste and sauté well until the raw smell disappears.

5
00:01:59,641 --> 00:02:25,544
Take 500 grams of chicken and mix it with the green chili paste. Add 1 tablespoon of red chili powder and let it marinate well.

6
00:02:28,210 --> 00:02:52,358
Add 0.5 tablespoon turmeric powder, 0.5 tablespoon biryani masala, and 0.5 cup of chopped coriander leaves.

7
00:02:55,447 --> 00:03:08,068
Add 1 cup of mint leaves, 10 cashew nuts, and 1 cup of curd.

8
00:03:31,389 --> 00:03:57,883
Take 2 cups of basmati rice and 2 cups of water.

9
00:03:57,883 --> 00:04:15,332
6 cardamoms.

